INSERT INTO `jos_community_groups_bulletins` VALUES (5,46,75,1,'Calling all digital divas, web chix & coder girls!','<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;\">The NCWIT Award for Aspirations in Computing honors young high school women active and interested in computing and technology. They are looking for next generation of technical talent. Award winners receive cool prizes, gadgets, scholarships and all girls can join a community of fellow technically-inclined young women. This is a great award to promote during your STARS outreach efforts! Visit the link below for more details:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;\"><a href=\"http://www.ncwit.org/award/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ncwit.org/award</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;\"><br /></span></p>','2011-09-21 03:03:14',''),(6,56,127,1,'ARTSI Alliance website','<p><a href=\"http://artsialliance.org/\">http://artsialliance.org/</a></p>','2011-10-04 20:15:27',''),(7,56,127,1,'Tekkotsu Wikki','<p><a href=\"http://wiki.tekkotsu.org/\">http://wiki.tekkotsu.org/</a></p>','2011-10-04 20:16:07',''),(26,79,73,1,'Celebration Leadership Planning Call - Reminder!','<p>Hi team! Just a reminder for our monthly Leadership Planning call on Monday 2/25 at 11:00am EST. Call in information is below:</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal;\">Conference line: 605-475-3200<br /> Passcode: 317844#</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal;\">*Please MUTE your phone!</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>Agenda:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Celebration website and CFP submission site - Ashley/Scott</li>\r\n<li>Committee Updates (if applicable)\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Program - Gloria/Polly</li>\r\n<li>Poster- Kinnis/Nikunja</li>\r\n<li>Local Arrangements - Nannette/Kristine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Review of project plan - Ashley</li>\r\n<li>Value added items discussion:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>business cards</li>\r\n<li>t-shirts</li>\r\n<li>ground transportation</li>\r\n<li>misc items</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Upcoming Information Session and prospective partners - Ashley/Teresa</li>\r\n<li>Next Meeting: Monday, March 25 - 11:00am EST</li>\r\n</ul>','2013-02-20 21:26:48','{\"filepermission-member\":0}'),(9,34,42,1,'UNC Charlotte GRAD open house','<p>Sorry for the short notice, but I never told the organizers that I could post this to STARS schools on our online community!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Have you considered graduate school in computing?  The College of Computing and Informatics at the University of North Carolina at Charlotte is holding an open house event, GRAD 2011, to introduce students to our graduate programs. We’ll introduce you to some of the research projects taking place in our Computer Science and Software and Information Systems departments, and discuss the options available to Masters and PhD students upon graduation.  Faculty and students will be on hand to answer any questions you may have.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">What: Graduate Research and Academic Discovery (GRAD 2011) open house event</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">When: Friday, November 4 -- Saturday, November 5</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Where: University of North Carolina at Charlotte, College of Computing and Informatics</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Details: Lodging for Thursday and Friday nights and all meals will be provided.  Travel costs of up to $50 can be reimbursed for out-of-area students.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">You can find more information about this event and register to attend at <a href=\"http://www.ccigrad.uncc.edu\">http://www.ccigrad.uncc.edu</a>. The registration deadline is Monday, Oct. 31.</p>\r\n</p>','2011-10-27 20:23:18',''),(10,30,42,1,'UNC Charlotte GRAD open house','<p>Sorry for the late notice, but I never told the organizers that I could post something to groups on our online community.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Have you considered graduate school in computing?  The College of Computing and Informatics at the University of North Carolina at Charlotte is holding an open house event, GRAD 2011, to introduce students to our graduate programs. We’ll introduce you to some of the research projects taking place in our Computer Science and Software and Information Systems departments, and discuss the options available to Masters and PhD students upon graduation.  Faculty and students will be on hand to answer any questions you may have.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">What: Graduate Research and Academic Discovery (GRAD 2011) open house event</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">When: Friday, November 4 -- Saturday, November 5</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Where: University of North Carolina at Charlotte, College of Computing and Informatics</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">Details: Lodging for Thursday and Friday nights and all meals will be provided.  Travel costs of up to $50 can be reimbursed for out-of-area students.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\">You can find more information about this event and register to attend at <a href=\"http://www.ccigrad.uncc.edu\">http://www.ccigrad.uncc.edu</a>. The registration deadline is Monday, Oct. 31.</p>\r\n</p>','2011-10-27 20:42:15',''),(11,45,75,1,'2012 NIH COMMUNITY COLLEGE SUMMER ENRICHMENT PROGRAM-Apply Now!','<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">2012 NIH Community College Summer Enrichment Program (CCSEP)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;\">The purpose of this program is to increase the number of community college students who participate in the NIH Summer Internship Program (SIP). The long-term goal is to increase the number of community college students who transfer to four-year colleges and universities and consider careers in the biomedical sciences.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p class=\"h2\" style=\"outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-color: initial; font-size: 13px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font: normal normal normal 1.13em/135% Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #666666; font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px initial initial;\">TO APPLY</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.2em; margin-left: 0px; outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; padding: 0px; border: 0px initial initial;\">To apply, you must complete the standard SIP application and indicate in your cover letter that you are applying for CCSEP.  Applications will open mid-November.  Deadline is January 15, 2012 at 5 pm EST.  Letters of reference must be received by January 31, 2012 at 5 pm EST.</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.2em; margin-left: 0px; outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 18px; padding: 0px; border: 0px initial initial;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 1.2em; margin-left: 0px; outline-width: 0px; outline-style: initial; outline-colo